dataIdInfo.idPurp: Suitable for use in a GIS database to display, locate, and query public municipal parks and protected open space in the City of Syracuse.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
This Syracuse Parks geographic dataset consists of polygon features representing parks in the City of Syracuse. The dataset includes 120 parks, some of which are owned by Onondaga County. Attributes describing each park's name, location, owner, facilities, and classification are included.

In addition, attributes pertaining to each park's primary tax parcel are included. The primary tax parcel is the tax parcel in the park where the major building, if one exists, is located. It is denoted by the attribute "TAX_ID." The tax parcel ID for any additional parcels that are also located in a given park are included. These IDs are included under the headings "TAX_ID2" through "TAX_ID7."
